# Global Standards

All code must follow best practices: accurate, readable, clean, and efficient.

## Comments

Use TSDoc for documentation. No `====` separators. No non-TSDoc comments.

### TSDoc Format

```tsx
/**
 * Brief description of the function/component.
 * @param paramName - Description of the parameter
 * @returns Description of the return value
 * @example
 * ```tsx
 * const result = myFunction('input');
 * ```
 */
```

###  Correct

```tsx
/**
 * Calculates the total price including tax.
 * @param price - The base price
 * @param taxRate - The tax rate as a decimal
 * @returns The total price with tax applied
 */
const calculateTotal = (price: number, taxRate: number): number => {
  return price * (1 + taxRate);
};
```

### Forbidden

```tsx
// This calculates total          ← Regular comment (not allowed)
// ==========================     ← Separator (not allowed)
/* Block comment */               ← Non-TSDoc block comment (not allowed)
```

## Styling

Never update global styles. Keep all styling local to components.
